	<div class="comment" id="c110135">
		<p>My mom made the best roast-beef hash; I never liked pot roast but loved the hash.  Her policy was that in any kind of hash there needs to be as much meat as other ingredients, total.  I have to agree and would use the larger quantity of corned beef to the smaller quantity of potatoes, etc. in your recipe.  I grew up with the canned kind of corned beef hash (looks a lot like canned dog food) and I always find homemade to be a little dry and crumbly.  I'm thinking a little of the cabbage, if there is any left over, added to the hash  might be good.  After all, the whole idea of hash is to use up whatever you have left over.</p>	
	</div>
