	<div class="comment" id="c110151">
		<p>I do my corned beef hash totally different. <br />
First I soften the onions in olive oil with a bit of garlic, add the corned beef and a bit of red wine, sometimes I add some beef stock, S&P... then I let it simmer for a bit. <br />
After that I put it in an oven dish and top it up with a good portion of mashed potatoes (with a hint of nutmeg and real butter). Sprinkle with grated cheese and breadcrumbs... 15/20 mins in oven and TA-DA! <br />
Corned beef hash is ready... at least that's what I called it all my life.</p>

<p>I'll have to try yours 'tho... I'm always looking for ideas for breakfast, and this one looks like a winner!</p>

